---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import LabSignup from '../components/LabSignup.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Intelligence OS"
  description="Editorial Intelligence OS is the practical operating system built from the discipline — frameworks, methods, assessments, guides and AI workflows that make Editorial Intelligence repeatable."
>
  <article class="container-site py-20">
    <div class="os-inner">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="t-label mb-6">The operating system</p>
        <h1 class="t-display mb-6">Editorial Intelligence OS</h1>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>Editorial Intelligence is the discipline of turning organisational evidence into better decisions, stronger narratives and reusable knowledge.</p>
          <p>Editorial Intelligence OS is the practical operating system built to make that discipline repeatable.</p>
          <p>It is the collection of frameworks, methods, assessments, guides, workflows and AI tools through which the discipline becomes something an organisation can actually use — consistently, at scale and over time.</p>
        </div>
      </header>

      <!-- Positioning hierarchy -->
      <div class="os-hierarchy mb-16">
        <a href="/intelligence" class="os-hier-item">
          <span class="os-hier-num">01</span>
          <div>
            <p class="os-hier-label">Editorial Intelligence</p>
            <p class="os-hier-sub">The discipline — the principles, the cycle, the evidence logic</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <div class="os-hier-connector">↓</div>
        <div class="os-hier-item os-hier-item--current">
          <span class="os-hier-num">02</span>
          <div>
            <p class="os-hier-label">Editorial Intelligence OS</p>
            <p class="os-hier-sub">The operating system — frameworks, methods, assessments, workflows</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="os-hier-connector">↓</div>
        <a href="/work" class="os-hier-item">
          <span class="os-hier-num">03</span>
          <div>
            <p class="os-hier-label">Consulting</p>
            <p class="os-hier-sub">Implementation — helping organisations build the capability</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Why the OS exists -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="os-h2 mb-6">Why the OS exists</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>A discipline without practical tools stays theoretical.</p>
          <p>Most organisations understand, in principle, that their evidence is underused. Research sits in reports. Customer insight lives in interview notes. Webinar and event conversations disappear into recordings. Market signals are noticed but not connected.</p>
          <p>The challenge is not persuading people that the problem exists. It is giving them a repeatable way to address it.</p>
          <p>Editorial Intelligence OS is that way. It translates the discipline's principles into tools that teams can learn, apply and return to as evidence accumulates and the organisation grows.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- What's included -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="os-h2 mb-8">What's included</h2>

        <div class="os-components">

          <div class="os-component-row">
            <div class="os-component-label-col">
              <span class="os-component-tag">Frameworks</span>
            </div>
            <div class="os-component-body">
              <p class="os-component-desc">Conceptual models for understanding how evidence becomes narrative, how narratives become assets, and how assets generate new evidence. Frameworks explain how to think about the problem.</p>
              <div class="os-component-links">
                <a href="/frameworks/editorial-intelligence-framework" class="os-link">EI Framework</a>
                <a href="/frameworks/evidence-engine" class="os-link">Evidence Engine</a>
                <a href="/frameworks/narrative-architecture" class="os-link">Narrative Architecture</a>
                <a href="/frameworks/editorial-activation" class="os-link">Editorial Activation</a>
                <a href="/frameworks/content-activation-framework" class="os-link">Content Activation</a>
                <a href="/frameworks/ai-visibility-buyability" class="os-link">AI Visibility & Buyability</a>
                <a href="/frameworks" class="os-link os-link--all">All frameworks →</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="os-component-row">
            <div class="os-component-label-col">
              <span class="os-component-tag">Assessment</span>
            </div>
            <div class="os-component-body">
              <p class="os-component-desc">A diagnostic tool for measuring Editorial Intelligence maturity across five dimensions: Capture, Connect, Synthesise, Activate and Learn. Identifies the strongest constraint and recommends where to focus first.</p>
              <a href="/assessment" class="os-link">Take the assessment →</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="os-component-row">
            <div class="os-component-label-col">
              <span class="os-component-tag">Applications</span>
            </div>
            <div class="os-component-body">
              <p class="os-component-desc">How the OS applies in practice — across research activation, customer evidence, webinar and event intelligence, AI workflows and specific organisational contexts.</p>
              <div class="os-component-links">
                <a href="/applications" class="os-link">Research, events and customer evidence</a>
                <a href="/applications/startups-scaleups" class="os-link">B2B startups and scaleups</a>
                <a href="/frameworks/editorial-intelligence-product-management" class="os-link">Product teams</a>
                <a href="/work/ai-visibility-audit" class="os-link">AI Visibility Audit</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="os-component-row">
            <div class="os-component-label-col">
              <span class="os-component-tag">Guides</span>
            </div>
            <div class="os-component-body">
              <p class="os-component-desc">Practical introductions to applying Editorial Intelligence in specific roles and contexts.</p>
              <a href="/guide" class="os-link">The AI-enabled content writer guide →</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="os-component-row">
            <div class="os-component-label-col">
              <span class="os-component-tag">AI workflows</span>
            </div>
            <div class="os-component-body">
              <p class="os-component-desc">Practical AI-assisted workflows for signal capture, synthesis, briefing, diagnostics and editorial review. AI accelerates evidence collection; Editorial Intelligence improves evidence interpretation.</p>
              <a href="/experiments" class="os-link">Active experiments and workflows →</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="os-component-row os-component-row--muted">
            <div class="os-component-label-col">
              <span class="os-component-tag os-component-tag--future">Coming</span>
            </div>
            <div class="os-component-body">
              <p class="os-component-desc os-component-desc--muted">Templates, signal-capture tools, evidence mapping canvas, courses, certification and software concepts are in development. The OS grows as the discipline matures.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Current state -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="os-h2 mb-6">Current state</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-6">
          <p>Editorial Intelligence OS is being built in public. The frameworks are live and in use. The assessment is operational. The applications and AI workflows are under active development.</p>
          <p>The OS is not finished. It is not supposed to be finished. Each new cycle of evidence — from client work, from the site itself, from Field Notes and the AI narrative series — strengthens the frameworks and surfaces the next tool to build.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/writing/the-site-is-the-proof" class="os-proof-link">How this site demonstrates the methodology in practice →</a>
        <LabSignup headline="See what the evidence changes" />
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Narratives -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="os-h2 mb-6">Evidence of the discipline</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-6">
          <p>The narratives on this site are evidence of Editorial Intelligence in practice. Each one shows how scattered signals — research, customer stories, webinars, market change — were connected into a strategic position that compounds over time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="os-narratives">
          <a href="/narratives/hidden-hours" class="os-narrative-item">
            <p class="os-narrative-title">Hidden Hours — Sage</p>
            <p class="os-narrative-desc">How one research programme was extended into an ongoing narrative platform, editorial series and source of market intelligence.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/narratives/winning-in-small" class="os-narrative-item">
            <p class="os-narrative-title">Winning in Small — Sage</p>
            <p class="os-narrative-desc">How event insight, customer stories and survey evidence were synthesised into a clearer strategic argument.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/narratives" class="os-narrative-item os-narrative-item--link">
            <p class="os-narrative-title">All narratives →</p>
            <p class="os-narrative-desc">The full library of strategic positions built from evidence.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Consulting -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="os-h2 mb-6">Working with me</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>I help organisations implement Editorial Intelligence — building the narrative systems, evidence workflows and editorial capability that turn distributed knowledge into a compounding strategic asset.</p>
          <p>Clients leave with narrative systems, evidence libraries, editorial workflows, knowledge assets and reusable thinking — not simply articles or reports.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/work" class="os-cta">Explore how we can work together →</a>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .os-inner {
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .prose-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .os-h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.35rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  /* ── Hierarchy ── */
  .os-hierarchy {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: stretch;
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .os-hier-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2.5rem 1fr;
    column-gap: 1rem;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }

  a.os-hier-item:hover {
    background: var(--color-surface-tertiary);
  }

  .os-hier-item--current {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 5%, var(--color-surface));
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 25%, var(--color-rule));
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 25%, var(--color-rule));
  }

  .os-hier-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .os-hier-label {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .os-hier-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .os-hier-connector {
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.3;
    padding: 0.35rem 0;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }

  /* ── Components grid ── */
  .os-components {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .os-component-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 7rem 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--color-rule);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }

  .os-component-row:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .os-component-row--muted {
    opacity: 0.65;
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .os-component-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .os-component-label-col {
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    padding: 1.25rem 1rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding-top: 1.4rem;
  }

  .os-component-body {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .os-component-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .os-component-tag--future {
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .os-component-desc {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .os-component-desc--muted {
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
  }

  .os-component-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  /* ── Links ── */
  .os-link {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    opacity: 0.8;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
    align-self: flex-start;
  }

  .os-link:hover { opacity: 1; }

  .os-link--all {
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .os-proof-link {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 35%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .os-proof-link:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent); }

  /* ── Narratives ── */
  .os-narratives {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .os-narrative-item {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
  }

  .os-narrative-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .os-narrative-item:hover { background: var(--color-surface-tertiary); }

  .os-narrative-title {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .os-narrative-item--link .os-narrative-title {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .os-narrative-desc {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── CTA ── */
  .os-cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 35%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 2px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .os-cta:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent); }
</style>
